PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article focuses on a study which evaluates the effects of perceived job stressors, job satisfaction and stressful life events on biochemical indicators of stress and a composite index of stress-related coronary disease risk. Researchers measured physiological indicators of stress such as high density lipids and systolic and diastolic blood pressure and estimated the risk of heart disease using the Framingham index. Details related to factors increasing the risk of heart disease and the results of the study are presented.
