TY  - JOUR
T1  - Impact of Exchange Variables on Exit, Voice, Loyalty, and Neglect: An Integrative Model of Responses to Declining Job Satisfaction
AU  - Rusbult, Caryl E.
AU  - Farrell, Dan
AU  - Rogers, Glen
AU  - Mainous, Arch G.
Y1  - 1988/09/01
PY  - 1988
DA  - 1988/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256461
DO  - 10.5465/256461
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 599
EP  - 627
VL  - 31
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This research offers a new theory predicting the effects of three exchange variables, job satisfaction, investment size, and quality of alternatives, on four general responses to dissatisfaction?exit, voice, loyalty, and neglect. Three studies designed to test model predictions' received good support. High satisfaction and investment encouraged voice and loyalty and discouraged exit and neglect. Satisfaction and investment interacted, with variations in investment most strongly promoting voice given high satisfaction. Better alternatives encouraged exit and voice and discouraged loyalty. However, there was no link between alternatives and neglect.
AB  - This research offers a new theory predicting the effects of three exchange variables, job satisfaction, investment size, and quality of alternatives, on four general responses to dissatisfaction?exit, voice, loyalty, and neglect. Three studies designed to test model predictions' received good support. High satisfaction and investment encouraged voice and loyalty and discouraged exit and neglect. Satisfaction and investment interacted, with variations in investment most strongly promoting voice given high satisfaction. Better alternatives encouraged exit and voice and discouraged loyalty. However, there was no link between alternatives and neglect.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/256461
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/256461
